    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is:  </p>\n<p>✅ <strong>Option A: Valine</strong></p>\n<h3>Explanation:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Essential amino acids</strong> are those that <strong>cannot be synthesized by the human body</strong> and must be obtained from the diet.  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Essential amino acids</strong>: Valine, Leucine, Isoleucine, Lysine, Methionine, Phenylalanine, Threonine, Tryptophan, and Histidine (in children/adults depending on context).</p></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Analysis of given options:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Valine</strong> → <em>Essential amino acid</em> ✅  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Proline</strong> → Non-essential (body can synthesize it) ❌  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Tyrosine</strong> → Non-essential (synthesized from phenylalanine) ❌  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Alanine</strong> → Non-essential ❌  </p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>✅ <strong>Answer: Valine (Option A)</strong></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
