    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mfo8xv7n/0dcd516b-9664-420a-9057-3b31916aaa87/6cb6b930-93ea-11f0-a2b3-1fa2d7fb2438/file-jaoe38c1mfo8xv7o.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mfo8xv7n/0dcd516b-9664-420a-9057-3b31916aaa87/6cb6b930-93ea-11f0-a2b3-1fa2d7fb2438/file-jaoe38c1mfo8xv7o.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"MHT CET (PCB) 2025 9th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 2 English Explanation\"><p>Glucose reacts with $\\mathrm{NH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$ to form an oxime which confirms the presence of carbonyl group in glucose.</p>",
