    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which amino acid from following contains highest number of N atoms in it?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Histidine\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Lysine\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " Arginine\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " Glutamine"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let’s remember that every α-amino acid has one nitrogen in its –NH₂ (amino) group on the α-carbon.  We only need to count how many additional N atoms are present in each side chain (R).</p>\n\n<p><p>General backbone: one N in –NH₂  </p></p>\n<p><p>Side-chain counts:</p>\n<p>• Histidine  </p>\n<p>– Imidazole ring contains 2 N  </p>\n<p>→ total N = 1 (backbone) + 2 = 3  </p>\n<p>• Lysine  </p>\n<p>– Side chain ends in –NH₂ (1 N)  </p>\n<p>→ total N = 1 + 1 = 2  </p>\n<p>• Arginine  </p>\n<p>– Guanidino group: –NH–C(=NH)–NH₂ has 3 N  </p>\n<p>→ total N = 1 + 3 = 4  </p>\n<p>• Glutamine  </p>\n<p>– Side chain amide –CONH₂ (1 N)  </p>\n<p>→ total N = 1 + 1 = 2  </p></p>\n\n<p>Arginine has the highest number of nitrogen atoms (4).  </p>\n<p>Answer: Option C, Arginine.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  }
